In[25]:
def draw_images(loader, size = 5):
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(size, size, figsize=(10,10))
    indexes = np.random.randint(low=0, high=len(loader.dataset), size=size*size)
    fig.suptitle("Garbage classification samples")
    for i in range(size):
        for j in range(size):
            idx = indexes[i * size + j]

            image, label = loader.dataset[idx]
            image = image.permute(1, 2, 0)
            image = image * torch.tensor([0.5, 0.5, 0.5]) + torch.tensor([0.5, 0.5, 0.5])
            image = image.clip(0, 1)

            axs[i, j].imshow(image)
            axs[i, j].axis('off')
            axs[i, j].set_title(f"{loader.dataset.dataset.classes[label]}")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

draw_images(train_loader)

#   
modified_layer_size = 512
dropout_coeff = 0.5

def resnet_34(num_classes : int, modified : bool = False):
    model = models.resnet34(weights = models.ResNet34_Weights.DEFAULT)
    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False
    layer = model.fc.in_features
    if modified:
      model.fc = nn.Sequential(nn.Dropout(dropout_coeff),
                               nn.Linear(layer, modified_layer_size),
                               nn.ReLU(),
                               nn.Linear(modified_layer_size, num_classes))
    else:
        model.fc = nn.Linear(layer, num_classes)

    return model

def mobilenet_v3(num_classes: int, modified: bool = False):
    #   
    model = models.mobilenet_v3_large(weights=models.MobileNet_V3_Large_Weights.DEFAULT)

    #   
    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False

    layer = model.classifier[0].in_features

    if modified:
        #      
        model.classifier = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Dropout(dropout_coeff),
            nn.Linear(layer, modified_layer_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(modified_layer_size, num_classes)
        )
    else:
        model.classifier = nn.Linear(layer, num_classes)

    return model

def efficientnet(num_classes: int, modified: bool = False):
    model = models.efficientnet_b0(weights=models.EfficientNet_B0_Weights.DEFAULT)

    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False

    layer = model.classifier[1].in_features

    if modified:
        model.classifier = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Dropout(dropout_coeff),
            nn.Linear(layer, modified_layer_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(modified_layer_size, num_classes)
        )
    else:
        model.classifier[1] = nn.Linear(layer, num_classes)

    return model

def googlenet(num_classes: int, modified: bool = False):
    model = models.googlenet(weights=models.GoogLeNet_Weights.DEFAULT)

    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False

    layer = model.fc.in_features

    if modified:
        model.fc = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Dropout(dropout_coeff),
            nn.Linear(layer, modified_layer_size),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(modified_layer_size, num_classes)
        )
    else:
        model.fc = nn.Linear(layer, num_classes)

    return model
In[27]:
def train(model, optimizer, train_loader, device=device):
    model.train()  #     
    train_losses = []
    train_accuracies = []

    start_time = time.time()
    for data in train_loader:
        images, labels = data[0].to(device), data[1].to(device) #           

        optimizer.zero_grad()  #  
        outputs = model(images)  #  

        loss = cross_entropy_loss(outputs, labels)  #  
        loss.backward()  #  
        optimizer.step()  #  

        train_losses.append(loss.item())

        accuracy = (torch.argmax(outputs, dim=1) == labels).float().mean()  #  
        train_accuracies.append(accuracy.item())

    train_time = time.time() - start_time
    avg_loss = sum(train_losses) / len(train_losses)  #  
    avg_accuracy = sum(train_accuracies) / len(train_accuracies)  #  

    return avg_loss, avg_accuracy, train_time

def valid(model, valid_loader, device=device):
    model.eval()  #     
    valid_losses = []
    valid_accuracies = []
    valid_f1_scores = []

    start_time = time.time()
    with torch.no_grad():
        for data in valid_loader:
            images, labels = data[0].to(device), data[1].to(device) #           
            outputs = model(images)
            loss = cross_entropy_loss(outputs, labels) # 

            valid_losses.append(loss.item())
            accuracy = (torch.argmax(outputs, dim=1) == labels).float().mean()  # 
            valid_accuracies.append(accuracy.item())

            f1 = f1_score(torch.argmax(outputs, dim=1).cpu(), labels.cpu(), average='macro')  # F1-
            valid_f1_scores.append(torch.tensor(f1))

    valid_time = time.time() - start_time
    avg_loss = sum(valid_losses) / len(valid_losses)  #  
    avg_accuracy = sum(valid_accuracies) / len(valid_accuracies)  #  

    return avg_loss, avg_accuracy, valid_time, valid_f1_scores

def test(model, test_loader, device=device):
    test_f1_scores = []
    with torch.no_grad():
        for data in test_loader:
            images, labels = data[0].to(device), data[1].to(device)
            outputs = model(images)
            f1 = f1_score(torch.argmax(outputs, dim=1).cpu(), labels.cpu(), average='macro')  # F1-
            test_f1_scores.append(torch.tensor(f1))
    return test_f1_scores
In[28]:
def get_time():
    t = time.localtime()
    #   
    return f"{t.tm_hour+3}:{time.strftime('%M:%S', t)}"

def make_exp(model):
    f1_valid = []
    optimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=learn_rate)  # 

    for epoch in range(epochs):
        print(f'Epoch {epoch + 1}/{epochs}')

        #  
        train_loss, train_accuracy, train_time = train(model, optimizer, train_loader)
        print(f"{get_time()}\tTrain\tLoss: {train_loss:.3f}\tAccuracy: {train_accuracy:.3f}\t\t\tTime: {train_time:.3f}s")

        #  
        valid_loss, valid_accuracy, valid_time, valid_f1_scores = valid(model, valid_loader)
        avg_valid_f1_score = torch.stack(valid_f1_scores).mean()
        print(f"{get_time()}\tValid\tLoss: {valid_loss:.3f}\tAccuracy: {valid_accuracy:.3f}\tF1: {avg_valid_f1_score:.3f}\tTime: {train_time:.3f}s")

        #  F1-  
        f1_valid.append(avg_valid_f1_score)

    #  
    test_f1_scores = test(model, test_loader)
    avg_test_f1_score = torch.stack(test_f1_scores).mean()
    print(f"{get_time()}\tTest\tF1: {avg_test_f1_score:.3f}")

    return f1_valid, avg_test_f1_score


def draw_f1_score(f1_score, model_name):
    x = range(epochs)
    plt.title(f"{model_name}")
    plt.plot(x, f1_score, marker="o")
    plt.xlabel("epoch")
    plt.ylabel("f1-score")
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()
